 BY LINUS CHIBUIKE TROOPS of Sector 3 Operation Lafiya Dole, on Saturday, 13 March, 2021, neutralised several Boko Haram Terrorists and their Islamic State West Africa Province counterparts, operating along the fringes of the Lake Chad and the Tumbus, and destroyed their gun trucks. The terrorists reportedly met their waterloo when they encountered the dogged troops who opened heavy fire and commenced pursuit. The development was disclosed in a statement by the Director of Army Public Relations, Brig. Gen. Mohammed Yerima. Unfortunately, he said, one officer and three gallant soldiers lost their lives in the operation, while others sustained injuries. The Army said the combined troops of the Sector who were on clearance patrol along the fringes of the Lake Chad had advanced and cleared Daban Massara and Ali Sherifti villages among other settlements before they harbored for replenishment and retrofitting. As they commenced the second phase of their operations and were advancing along the Kukawa-Monguno Road, about 14 kilometers to their base, the statement said they sighted BHTs/ISWAP gun trucks and swiftly commenced pursuit with heavy fire and deft manouver. “In the course of the hot pursuit, which was aided by air cover provided by the Air Task Team of Operation Lafia Dole, several terrorists were neutralised and their gun trucks destroyed,” it added. The Army noted, “Unfortunately however, one officer and three gallant soldiers paid the Supreme sacrifices while those wounded in action are currently receiving medical attention at 7 Division Medical Services and Hospital in Maimalari Cantonment. “Above is on-the-spot account of the encounter between Nigerian troops and the Boko Haram/ISWAP terrorists in Mugono area and environ.” “Members of the public are assured that the troops are on top of the situation and working assiduously to end the insurgency and terrorism in the country in line with the directives of the Chief of Army Staff,” Yerima said. 